'''''The Bounty Hunter Wars''''' trilogy was written by [[K. W. Jeter]]. It details the events of [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]], [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]], [[Kateel of Kuhlvult|Neelah]], and [[Kuat (person)|Kuat of Kuat]] starting just days after the [[Battle of the Great Pit of Carkoon|battle]] at [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] and Boba Fett's escape from the [[Sarlacc/Legends|sarlacc]] pit. The trilogy makes extensive use of [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] characters from [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] and ''[[Tales of the Bounty Hunters]]'', including [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]], [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]], [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]], and [[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]].

The trilogy also has flashbacks to scenes set just after [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], in which Boba Fett, Bossk, [[Kuat of Kuat/Legends|Kuat of Kuat]] and [[Prince/Legends|Prince]] [[Xizor/Legends|Xizor]] are the main characters.

The series opened with ''[[The Mandalorian Armor]]'' in June 1998 and concluded in July 1999 with ''[[Hard Merchandise]]''.

In 1999 the [[Science Fiction Book Club]] published an omnibus of the trilogy in hardback.

